column5: How do you know a walleye that size taste like leather?? I guess by your coment is that YOU have killed one that size to say it tastes bad, or are you just posting for the hell of it? Do everybody a favour and keep your comments to yourself, because you are the one that sounds like an
Nice fishes, get out the Fish Crisp mmmmmmmmmmm.
Nate Why are your posts so negative? From your other postings that I have seen from you are negative. This is not a FF.net site.  Nice eyes BTW
Wow, what a great first outing!  You're gonna have a tough time topping that one, Grant.  Thanks for the post!
Awesome 'eyes! Looks like you guys had a good haul.  keep the big fish reports coming.  -Ramble
ahaha I like that comment.. I used to be on that site years ago but left when all the grumpy old men got to annoying  ..
Excellent report and pic's... WTG guys...

I forgot one big happy loving family here...  Paze, I don't eat fish but I can only imagine what an 11lb walleye that's been cruising a lake eating mercury and other toxins for years must taste like  As for your comment City fisher...sure it had nothing to do with a out of season trout report you posted and admitted to?...Nah couldn't have anything to do with that  Nate (runs to prepare for Team OFC tongue lashing)
Very nice... well done.... no real fishing here till the first...  and toungue lashing... hey.. around here???  LOL
Wow Grant now that is some set of eyes.What a way to make up for lack of fall Quinte walleye
You did a good job. Grant. Thanks again for the report.

Could it be possiible for a 10lb walleye from BOQ to be less than 10yrs of age? Maybe 7-8yrs because it's from lake Ontario where it has more food and grows quicker. Where as a 6+lb walleye from the kawartha might be older and has more toxic? Just curious to know.

Hey all,  Here are a few pics from my first hardwater outing of the season. We fished on 3.5-5 inches of GOOD ice with real nice conditions. The highlight of our day came just before 5pm when my good friend nailed a 11lber. He had never caught a walleye like that so this entire trip was dedicated to him catching one. All in all we had a great day; landing 4 eyes, 1 pike and a bunch of jumbos. We also lost a tonne of fish as most of the time they were hitting on the way down and which didn't give us much time to set the hook before they spit it. Here are the pics.
Some very nice fish there, congrats to you both! Thanks for sharing.
Nice fish, that 11 lber. is a pig.
Wow, very impressive.  Way to go  Joey
awesome post....looks like you had a good day!!!
Top shelf bud, those're some impressive fish!
Good going nice looking eyes  rob
great work thanks for the post.
N I C E    F I S H !!!!!!!!.  ...right on guys ...great fishing for sure awesome pics too !!.  .i cant wait till sunday,then its my turn cheers
Congrats to you and yur buddy for his bigun. You know what they say about first ice....AWESOME.
I think I'd be a bit nervous on 3.5-5" of ice with my quad!  nice going on the fish though, beauties!!  Sinker
some nice ones,congrats
Wow...what an incredible report!  Some great looking fish and judging from the smiles, a great day was had out there.  Great job!
Why on earth would you kill an 11 lb walleye to eat?  I can go down to the store and season a nice peice of leather work boot if you'd like instead?  It would probably taste very similar  Nate

Hey Nate,  I knew that issue was going to come up. The hole was not large enough so we were forced use a gaff. I am not very comfortable killing fish of that size nor do I condone it. Funny enough, I don't even eat fish. However, given the circumstances that were presented at that moment; I did not have any other alternative. I am very sorry if you found that offensive.
nice looking catch...dont let keeping that 11lber bother u.  You did what u had to do
A good outing and a beaut first catch for your buddy...
Excellent report and pics! Some beautiful fish too!
Good Stuff Bud...  Good to see you guys wearing pfd's as well

Hey Grant don't ever worry about explaining yourself for keep a completly legal fish on here. No matter what you post someone will complain about it.  Great report and fish, and Thanks for posting the report.  Mike
Thanks for the report. I find the big eyes taste just as good as the little ones.
great report ! .. thats a great bunch of fish ! If you need a partner one day gimme a shout !

I suppose unhooking it at the hole was impossible?    people say oh don't let what others say bother you because you legally can keep walleye that size, yet when the guy killed a musky to eat they ripped his head off...  's  Nate

I wouldn't have kept it either, but I agree with bassman that they taste as good.  Comparing it with shoe leather is a bit of an exaggeration IMO.  I always enjoy reading some of the rants here, like keeping fish or taking OOS pictures.  Thanks for keeping things interesting here!
VN!
